[codex] 34:RESPONSE: The Introduction and General Discussion now draw on more contemporary work in the feedback, goalΓÇæsetting, and socialΓÇænorms literatures (e.g., Locke & Latham, 2019; Itzchakov & Latham, 2018; Chen, Latham, & Piccolo, 2020; Schultz, Nolan, & Cialdini, 2018; Devine & Ash, 2022; Andor, Gerster, & Peters, 2020; Henry, Ferraro, & Kontoleon, 2019; Mertens & Schultz, 2021), alongside the foundational citations from our original manuscript, which we have retained. We have also expanded our IntroductionΓÇÖs theorizing (pp. XΓÇæX) to clarify why descriptive feedback should shift selection decisions about women and underrepresented minorities even without a paired explicit goal: we argue that there is a strong, implicit injunctive norm in this setting against prejudiced selection, and feedback makes prior behavior that could be interpreted as prejudiced salient alongside that implicit norm, which provokes behavior change. We address Reviewer 1ΓÇÖs specific suggestions in detail on Pages X-X of this response letter.
